[normal]&#xa0;
[normal](a)
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]An application is made to the Secretary of State for the exemption order;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal](b)
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]The Secretary of State must then consult the Disabled Persons Transport Advisory Committee and such other persons as he thinks appropriate before:
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal](i)
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]making an exemption order in the terms of the application for the order;
[normal](ii)
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]making an exemption order in such other terms as the Secretary of State thinks appropriate; or
[normal](iii)
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]refusing
[normal] to make an exemption order.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal](c)
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]The Secretary of State must then consult the Disabled Persons Transport Advisory Committee before deciding which parliamentary procedure available is to be adopted in connection with the making of the exemption order. There are two options: the draft affirmative resolution and the negative resolution procedure.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal](d)
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]The negative resolution procedure can only be made if the Secretary of State has, after consulting the Disabled Persons Transport Advisory Committee, 
[normal]and other appropriate persons, made regulations, governing the procedure, which are themselves subject to the draft affirmative resolution procedure.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal](a)
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Applications for exemptions will be published online, together with any accompanying documents;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal](b)
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]The Disabled Persons Transport Advisory Committee will continue to provide its opinion on whether the exemption should be granted;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal](c)
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]The decision, together with the terms of the exemption, will also be published online.
